WEBVTT

00:13.140 --> 00:16.230
Man: We need to hurry.Charlie. She's sick.

00:16.710 --> 00:17.540
He needs surgery.

00:17.740 --> 00:18.720
That's your kid,
isn't it?

00:18.920 --> 00:20.110
When Finch wakes up,

00:20.310 --> 00:22.030
we're going to take him away
from this place.

00:22.230 --> 00:23.980
Her name is Shrike.
She works for PADRE.

00:24.180 --> 00:26.120
He wanted her to find a way to
stop the effect of walker bites.

00:26.320 --> 00:28.210
What kind of treatment?Radiation.

00:28.410 --> 00:30.430
It was worse than dying
from the bites.

00:30.630 --> 00:32.560
I have faith you'll
get it right this time.

00:32.760 --> 00:34.260
I'm going to kill you!

00:34.460 --> 00:36.740
Girl: I want to be a part
of the future PADRE's building.

00:36.940 --> 00:37.740
PADRE: <i>I'm glad to hear that.</i>

00:37.940 --> 00:39.390
Can you pull over?!

00:39.590 --> 00:40.820
Woman: Morgan, go!

00:50.520 --> 00:52.840
♪[Walker growling]

00:53.040 --> 00:55.190
♪

00:55.390 --> 00:57.630
[Gasps]

00:57.830 --> 01:00.850
♪

01:01.050 --> 01:03.200
[Breathing heavily]

01:03.400 --> 01:06.330
[Growling continues]

01:06.530 --> 01:09.640
[Grunts]

01:09.840 --> 01:12.080
Guard: You're awake.

01:12.280 --> 01:15.300
Good.

01:15.500 --> 01:19.080
Sorry about the sedative,
but it's easier that way.

01:19.280 --> 01:21.040
How long are you gonna
keep me here?

01:21.240 --> 01:23.170
Haven't you taken
enough blood?

01:23.370 --> 01:26.000
We've moved beyond
studying your blood.

01:26.200 --> 01:28.830
[Growling continues]What does that mean?

01:29.030 --> 01:31.310
It'll be easier for Blue Jay
to explain that.

01:31.510 --> 01:33.660
[Door opens, closes]

01:33.860 --> 01:36.400
[Growling continues]

01:36.600 --> 01:38.540
♪

01:38.740 --> 01:40.760
Naomi?

01:40.960 --> 01:42.320
That was a long time ago.

01:42.520 --> 01:44.630
♪

01:44.830 --> 01:46.150
You two know one another?

01:46.350 --> 01:47.890
Shrike didn't mention that.

01:48.090 --> 01:49.900
♪

01:50.100 --> 01:51.770
PADRE wants me back
at the Island.

01:51.970 --> 01:53.290
Get her ready.

01:53.490 --> 01:56.900
♪

01:57.100 --> 01:58.860
[Growling continues]

01:59.060 --> 01:59.730
You're part of this, too.

01:59.930 --> 02:01.860
Not by choice.

02:02.060 --> 02:04.040
You the one who had them drawing
my blood all those years?

02:04.240 --> 02:05.390
It wasn't me.

02:05.590 --> 02:08.260
I didn't even know
you were alive, Madison,

02:08.460 --> 02:10.700
until Shrike
just gave me your records.

02:10.900 --> 02:12.300
What happens now?

02:13.780 --> 02:15.180
I've done everything I can
to put her off.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.270
From what?
What is she gonna do to me?

02:17.470 --> 02:20.000
[Growling continues]

02:22.440 --> 02:25.410
Shrike has ideas
on how to heal Carrion bites.

02:25.610 --> 02:27.240
They're based on Alicia
surviving a bite

02:27.440 --> 02:28.800
as long as she did.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.150
Jesus.

02:30.350 --> 02:32.590
[Growling continues]

02:32.790 --> 02:34.290
And now
she wants to test it.

02:34.490 --> 02:36.290
That's probably why
she was collecting your blood.

02:36.490 --> 02:38.730
She thought maybe it was
something besides the radiation,

02:38.930 --> 02:40.470
something hereditary.

02:40.670 --> 02:42.330
Could she be right?

02:44.510 --> 02:47.390
Anything's possible,
but there's a --

02:47.590 --> 02:49.870
there's a boy who seems to be
responding to the radiation,

02:50.070 --> 02:52.870
but it hasn't even
been a week.

02:53.070 --> 02:55.400
If I don't do this,
Shrike will,

02:55.600 --> 02:57.700
and your chances of it
working are better with me.

02:57.900 --> 03:01.230
[Growling continues]

03:01.430 --> 03:02.970
Can I ask you a favor?

03:03.170 --> 03:04.100
Anything.

03:04.300 --> 03:05.670
There's a file
back on the island.

03:05.870 --> 03:07.800
A file?

03:08.000 --> 03:09.720
It's got the names of the kids
I took when I was a Collector.

03:09.910 --> 03:13.020
Not the names PADRE gave them,
but their real names.

03:13.220 --> 03:14.330
And where
I took them from.

03:14.530 --> 03:16.200
What do you want me
to do with it?

03:16.400 --> 03:19.550
What I promised Mo
I'd do.

03:19.750 --> 03:21.420
Help track down
these kids' parents.

03:21.620 --> 03:22.990
Every good thing
I've tried to

03:23.190 --> 03:25.980
since I've been at PADRE
has blown up in my face.

03:28.160 --> 03:29.710
I know the feeling.

03:29.910 --> 03:31.430
<i>It's Shrike.</i>
<i>Is she ready?</i>

03:31.630 --> 03:33.910
♪

03:34.110 --> 03:35.440
She's ready.

03:35.640 --> 03:39.570
♪

03:39.770 --> 03:43.440
I left you once at the stadium,
and you saved us all.

03:43.640 --> 03:45.100
I will not leave you now.

03:45.300 --> 03:47.010
I'll be right here
until the end.

03:47.210 --> 03:48.750
♪

03:48.950 --> 03:51.240
[Growling continues]

03:51.430 --> 03:59.290
♪

03:59.490 --> 04:07.340
♪

04:07.540 --> 04:15.380
♪

04:19.650 --> 04:21.910
[Indistinct
conversations][Seagulls
squawking]

04:26.260 --> 04:28.920
Wow.

04:29.120 --> 04:30.830
Cool.

04:34.700 --> 04:36.110
Man.

04:36.310 --> 04:38.240
We shouldn't be in here.

04:38.440 --> 04:40.360
There weren't any guards
outside.

04:42.970 --> 04:46.770
PADRE:
<i>What are you doing in here?!</i>
[Both gasp]

04:46.970 --> 04:49.290
We need
to get out of here.

04:49.490 --> 04:51.730
[Laughs] "What are you
doing in here?"

04:51.930 --> 04:53.820
Dad. Not funny.

04:54.020 --> 04:55.170
You should have seen
your faces.

04:55.370 --> 04:56.870
Yeah, we did, in that.

04:57.070 --> 04:58.740
Which, by the way,
is creepy.

04:58.940 --> 05:00.700
It's not so bad.

05:00.900 --> 05:02.520
It lets me keep an eye on things
when I'm in meetings.

05:02.720 --> 05:04.830
Also, you've gotta get
that mic fixed.

05:05.030 --> 05:06.530
Yeah, you're gonna freak
people out with that.

05:06.730 --> 05:07.620
Sergeant Brenner says
it's probably

05:07.820 --> 05:09.050
just a faulty wire.

05:09.250 --> 05:11.790
I'll get it
taken care of.

05:11.990 --> 05:13.530
You really have to go
today?

05:15.270 --> 05:17.580
I do.

05:17.780 --> 05:18.880
Why?

05:20.400 --> 05:22.410
[Sighs] Come with me.

05:22.610 --> 05:25.590
I want to show you guys
something.

05:25.790 --> 05:27.320
Come on.

05:30.760 --> 05:31.990
A woodpecker?

05:32.190 --> 05:33.340
Krennick: Look closer.

05:33.540 --> 05:35.030
The red marking
on its head.

05:35.230 --> 05:38.170
It's a middle-spotted
woodpecker.

05:38.370 --> 05:41.740
So?
What's the big deal?

05:41.940 --> 05:44.570
Remember what your mom said
when she gave me these?

05:44.770 --> 05:47.440
"So you'll always see
what's coming."

05:47.640 --> 05:49.920
When I looked through them
and saw that bird this morning,

05:50.120 --> 05:51.790
felt like she was trying
to tell us something.

05:51.990 --> 05:53.230
What?

05:53.430 --> 05:56.450
That we were
gonna be okay here.

05:56.650 --> 05:58.800
These birds,
they live in families.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.230
They cooperate to raise
their young.

06:00.430 --> 06:03.110
If they can do it, so can we.

06:03.310 --> 06:05.930
General Krennick,
should we load up, sir?

06:09.020 --> 06:10.580
Give us a minute.

06:14.850 --> 06:17.380
I hate when you leave
the island.

06:17.580 --> 06:19.640
That's the way we're gonna help
people rebuild.

06:19.840 --> 06:21.120
How?

06:21.320 --> 06:22.430
The same way we built
this place.

06:22.630 --> 06:24.340
The shipping containers.

06:24.540 --> 06:27.090
Each one is filled with enough
supplies for folks to rebuild.

06:27.290 --> 06:28.310
It's dangerous
out there.

06:28.500 --> 06:29.960
I mean, Atlanta was bombed.
And L.A.

06:30.160 --> 06:32.090
We need to enact
our distribution protocols.

06:32.290 --> 06:34.310
We need to seed
new communities, Ben.

06:34.510 --> 06:36.620
That's the way the program
was designed.

06:36.820 --> 06:38.920
But how do you even know
there's still people out there?

06:39.120 --> 06:40.880
Right.You remember Elias?

06:41.080 --> 06:42.140
Senator Vasquez?

06:42.340 --> 06:43.230
We made contact
with him yesterday.

06:43.430 --> 06:44.630
He and his staff
are in a bunker

06:44.830 --> 06:46.670
beneath the Franklin Hotel
in Galveston.

06:46.870 --> 06:47.890
They're safe.

06:48.090 --> 06:49.720
So then, why can't you
do the same thing?

06:49.920 --> 06:52.330
Why can't you stay here
on the island, until it's safer?

06:52.530 --> 06:53.500
Look,
we'll never survive here

06:53.700 --> 06:55.720
if it's just us cut off
from the world.

06:55.920 --> 06:57.290
What'll happen when
our supplies run out

06:57.490 --> 06:59.070
if we don't have
trading partners?

06:59.270 --> 07:01.200
Other communities to rely on?

07:02.980 --> 07:05.550
[Sighs] Don't worry.
You're gonna be safe here.

07:08.680 --> 07:10.870
Remember, if we
communicate by radio,

07:11.070 --> 07:12.570
I want you to use
those code names I gave you.

07:12.770 --> 07:15.310
The bird names?It's for your safety.

07:15.510 --> 07:17.090
I'm Crane, right?

07:17.290 --> 07:18.090
That's right.

07:18.290 --> 07:20.360
Why do I
have to be Shrike?

07:20.560 --> 07:21.970
'Cause a shrike
may be small,

07:22.170 --> 07:24.320
but it is brutal
when it needs to be.

07:24.520 --> 07:26.660
Doesn't hesitate
to look after its family.

07:29.050 --> 07:30.540
I'll be right back.

07:30.740 --> 07:32.150
I want you to keep
your brother safe

07:32.350 --> 07:33.800
while I'm gone,
you hear me?

07:36.840 --> 07:38.900
♪

07:39.100 --> 07:40.460
Come here.

07:40.660 --> 07:47.040
♪

07:47.240 --> 07:48.520
I'll see you soon.

07:48.720 --> 07:53.780
♪

07:53.980 --> 07:59.050
♪

07:59.250 --> 08:02.880
[Growling]

08:03.080 --> 08:06.230
After everything PADRE
gave you, you betrayed him.

08:06.430 --> 08:09.060
This is how you're gonna
make it up to him.

08:09.260 --> 08:10.840
And you won't be alone.

08:11.040 --> 08:12.970
Nightingale is gonna be
right here next to you.

08:13.170 --> 08:14.760
As soon as we can find him.

08:14.960 --> 08:17.680
Why is PADRE doing this?

08:17.870 --> 08:20.290
The same reason
he does everything.

08:20.490 --> 08:23.250
To ensure what
he's built endures.

08:23.450 --> 08:27.950
[Growling continues]

08:28.150 --> 08:30.380
[Grunts]Dove: Wren, stop.

08:30.580 --> 08:34.430
Do you realize how far we are
from the rest of the troop?

08:34.630 --> 08:37.390
I need to do this.

08:37.590 --> 08:39.170
Do what?

08:42.560 --> 08:43.950
We need to see
what's in there.

08:45.480 --> 08:48.490
[Growling continues]

08:48.690 --> 08:51.320
Shrike:
Years from now, when people
look back and wonder

08:51.520 --> 08:53.750
how PADRE was able
to stop infections

08:53.950 --> 08:57.500
from Carrion bites
from killing,

08:57.700 --> 09:01.200
they'll remember today.[Growling continues]

09:01.400 --> 09:04.330
And you'll be a hero.

09:04.530 --> 09:07.640
I think
Finch might be inside.

09:07.840 --> 09:08.860
Finch?

09:09.060 --> 09:10.290
He never came back
from his surgery.

09:10.490 --> 09:12.430
Because
he's still recovering.

09:12.620 --> 09:14.430
You really
believe that?

09:14.630 --> 09:15.780
Why wouldn't I?

09:15.980 --> 09:16.820
After his transport boat
got attacked,

09:17.020 --> 09:18.650
PADRE sent guards
after him.

09:18.850 --> 09:20.780
I checked the logs,
Dove.

09:20.980 --> 09:22.570
It says they went to
the old railroad museum,

09:22.770 --> 09:24.830
but there was
nothing there.

09:25.030 --> 09:26.740
I think someone must've moved
the train car here.

09:26.940 --> 09:28.310
Why would someone
do that?I don't know.

09:28.510 --> 09:30.360
Maybe PADRE isn't telling us
the truth.

09:30.560 --> 09:32.790
♪

09:32.990 --> 09:35.140
What if something bad
happened in there?

09:35.340 --> 09:36.800
What if
it's still happening?

09:37.000 --> 09:39.150
♪

09:39.350 --> 09:40.450
[Growling continues]

09:40.650 --> 09:41.890
June: Shrike, wait.

09:42.090 --> 09:44.460
At least let me sedate her.

09:44.660 --> 09:45.680
No.

09:45.880 --> 09:47.370
She's brought PADRE
plenty of pain.

09:47.570 --> 09:49.550
[Growling continues]

09:49.750 --> 09:51.200
It's time she felt
a little herself.

09:51.400 --> 09:53.250
No.

09:53.450 --> 09:54.730
[Growling continues]

09:54.930 --> 09:56.690
No. [Grunts]

09:56.890 --> 09:58.250
♪

09:58.450 --> 10:00.340
What the hell
are you doing?

10:00.540 --> 10:02.520
Mo: We have to see
what's going on in there.

10:02.720 --> 10:03.690
What are you doing?

10:03.890 --> 10:05.480
Wren.

10:05.680 --> 10:06.830
Come back here!

10:07.030 --> 10:08.260
♪

10:08.460 --> 10:10.610
[Growling continues]

10:10.810 --> 10:14.270
[Grunting]

10:14.470 --> 10:15.530
No.

10:15.730 --> 10:18.100
[Grunts]

10:18.300 --> 10:20.360
Mo: Shrike!

10:20.560 --> 10:23.630
Stop! Let her go!

10:23.830 --> 10:25.410
Get her out of here.
Now.

10:25.610 --> 10:27.850
[Growling continues]

10:28.050 --> 10:31.550
♪

10:31.750 --> 10:32.940
[Grunts]

10:33.140 --> 10:35.070
Blue Jay, help me!

10:35.270 --> 10:36.730
Blue Jay!

10:36.930 --> 10:38.080
♪

10:38.280 --> 10:41.950
[Growling stops]

10:42.150 --> 10:44.470
Thanks.I owed you one.

10:44.670 --> 10:46.080
[Gun clicks]

10:46.280 --> 10:48.130
[Grunts]

10:48.330 --> 10:50.740
Madison: [Grunts]

10:50.940 --> 10:58.530
♪

10:58.730 --> 11:01.140
[Grunts]

11:01.340 --> 11:03.230
The hell
are you doing here?

11:03.430 --> 11:06.060
We just have to get out of here
so we can do what we said.

11:06.260 --> 11:07.320
I'm never gonna be able to get
near the island after this.

11:07.520 --> 11:09.720
We'll find a way.
My dad, he can help.

11:09.920 --> 11:11.980
No, he can't help us
right now.

11:12.180 --> 11:13.680
Why not?Doesn't matter.

11:13.880 --> 11:15.110
Until he's back,
we're on our own.

11:15.310 --> 11:17.770
[Gunfire]

11:17.970 --> 11:25.470
♪

11:25.670 --> 11:26.910
We just have to get through
to the prefects

11:27.110 --> 11:28.560
the way you got through
to me.

11:28.760 --> 11:30.610
We do that,
the other kids will follow.

11:30.810 --> 11:32.300
It's not gonna be easy,
Mo.

11:32.500 --> 11:35.130
Here, Madison.Thanks.

11:35.330 --> 11:36.920
[Inhales deeply]

11:37.120 --> 11:38.940
♪

11:39.140 --> 11:40.920
<i>Shrike, it's Hawk.</i>
<i>We're done for the day,</i>

11:41.120 --> 11:43.320
<i>and we're headed back</i>
<i>to the island.</i>

11:43.510 --> 11:44.840
Shit.

11:45.040 --> 11:48.580
♪

11:48.780 --> 11:51.370
[Gun clicks]Don't move.

11:51.570 --> 11:53.370
Call the prefects.

11:53.570 --> 11:56.680
Tell them
to get more guards.

11:56.880 --> 11:59.030
Don't.
She was going to kill Lark.

11:59.230 --> 12:00.290
She deserved it.

12:00.490 --> 12:01.860
Did Finch?

12:02.060 --> 12:04.640
Don't listen to her.

12:04.840 --> 12:07.030
You killed him,
didn't you?

12:07.230 --> 12:08.040
I saved his life.

12:08.240 --> 12:09.780
That is a lie.

12:09.980 --> 12:11.950
♪

12:12.150 --> 12:13.910
Where is he?

12:14.110 --> 12:16.040
Somewhere his parents
can't do him anymore harm.

12:16.240 --> 12:20.270
She's the reason
Finch got bit.

12:20.460 --> 12:21.830
Finch got bit?

12:22.030 --> 12:23.660
♪

12:23.860 --> 12:25.880
Shrike, what the hell
is going on here?

12:26.080 --> 12:28.100
I am protecting
what PADRE's built.

12:28.300 --> 12:30.280
I'm ensuring you kids
have a future,

12:30.470 --> 12:31.840
a future --Is that what this
looks like to you?

12:32.040 --> 12:34.320
♪

12:34.520 --> 12:37.200
Hawk:
<i>Dove, what's your location?</i>

12:37.390 --> 12:39.240
Tell them where we are.
Tell them to get over here.

12:39.440 --> 12:40.630
Don't do it, Dove.

12:40.830 --> 12:42.200
Why not?

12:42.400 --> 12:43.720
PADRE lied about this.

12:43.920 --> 12:45.640
Think about what else
he's lied to you about.

12:45.840 --> 12:47.030
Your parents --
they could still be out there,

12:47.230 --> 12:48.690
and I can help you
find them.

12:48.880 --> 12:50.030
I don't want to find
my parents.

12:50.230 --> 12:52.430
They abandoned me.
They couldn't take care of me.

12:52.630 --> 12:54.210
That's not true.

12:54.410 --> 12:56.170
How do you know?

12:56.370 --> 12:58.000
Because I'm the one who took
you away from your parents.

12:58.200 --> 13:00.570
♪

13:00.770 --> 13:02.350
W-What were their names?

13:02.550 --> 13:04.530
Where did you take me from?

13:04.730 --> 13:08.270
I don't know,
but I know your face.

13:08.470 --> 13:09.790
She's trying
to trick you.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.710
The only one tricking you
is PADRE.

13:11.910 --> 13:13.710
She's right, Dove.

13:13.910 --> 13:15.540
That's why PADRE kept
all of this secret,

13:15.740 --> 13:17.240
so none of you would know.

13:17.430 --> 13:19.630
But we can change that.

13:19.830 --> 13:20.670
How?

13:20.870 --> 13:22.590
I just need to get
to the island.

13:22.790 --> 13:23.890
There's a file there.

13:24.090 --> 13:25.500
It has all the names
of the kids I took

13:25.700 --> 13:26.590
and where
I took them from.

13:26.790 --> 13:27.900
That's how
I can help you.

13:28.100 --> 13:29.730
That's how I can help
all the kids.

13:29.930 --> 13:31.120
<i>Dove, do you copy?</i>

13:31.320 --> 13:32.900
<i>Where are you?</i>

13:33.100 --> 13:40.040
♪

13:40.240 --> 13:41.260
I'll help you get back
to the island.

13:41.460 --> 13:42.910
Dove --

13:43.110 --> 13:44.870
I don't care about
what's in that file,

13:45.070 --> 13:46.180
but I do care about
the truth,

13:46.380 --> 13:48.050
and I want to hear it
from PADRE.

13:48.250 --> 13:51.790
♪

13:51.990 --> 13:53.710
You'll never get past
the guards.

13:53.910 --> 13:55.360
We will if you help us.

13:55.560 --> 13:56.880
Why would I do that?

13:57.080 --> 14:00.060
♪

14:00.260 --> 14:01.760
You kill me,

14:01.960 --> 14:03.150
and PADRE will do
way worse

14:03.350 --> 14:04.940
than I planned to do
to Lark today.

14:05.130 --> 14:07.850
And why is that?

14:08.050 --> 14:09.680
Because
I'm PADRE's daughter.

14:09.880 --> 14:15.160
♪

14:15.360 --> 14:20.600
♪

14:20.800 --> 14:21.870
We got our work
cut out for us.

14:22.060 --> 14:26.220
But we're starting
from a good place.

14:26.420 --> 14:27.510
Let's move it out.

14:30.300 --> 14:31.440
Are they gone?

14:31.640 --> 14:33.040
Yeah.

14:43.090 --> 14:44.190
We shouldn't be here.

14:44.390 --> 14:46.240
I just want to make sure
he's safe.

14:46.440 --> 14:48.460
He will be.

14:48.660 --> 14:50.230
Oh, shit.

14:52.800 --> 14:54.160
Dad forgot these.

14:54.360 --> 14:56.120
So?

14:56.320 --> 14:58.160
We have to
take them to him.

14:58.360 --> 15:00.080
No, Ben.

15:00.280 --> 15:01.470
Well, how's he supposed to see
what's coming without them?

15:01.670 --> 15:03.210
It's just
a superstition.

15:03.410 --> 15:05.210
He's got every other adult
on the island with him.

15:05.410 --> 15:06.430
He'll be fine.

15:06.630 --> 15:07.650
That's what we thought
about Mom.

15:07.850 --> 15:08.650
Stay on the boat.

15:08.850 --> 15:10.780
Get out of my way,
Sam.

15:10.980 --> 15:12.000
No.

15:12.200 --> 15:13.830
♪

15:14.030 --> 15:15.430
[Grunting]Get out of my way.

15:17.690 --> 15:19.010
Ben!

15:19.210 --> 15:20.140
Ben.

15:20.340 --> 15:28.370
♪

15:28.570 --> 15:36.800
♪

15:37.890 --> 15:40.070
You're making
a big mistake,

15:40.270 --> 15:42.680
Whatever answer
you think you want,

15:42.880 --> 15:44.030
it's not
what you think.

15:46.070 --> 15:48.600
[Guns click]Woman: Hands up.

15:48.800 --> 15:51.250
[Man speaks indistinctly]

15:52.510 --> 15:55.260
Tell us what we want to know.
Nobody has to get hurt.

15:55.460 --> 15:56.440
Wait, I know you.

15:56.640 --> 15:59.440
I can't place where,
but I do.

15:59.640 --> 16:01.180
And you were living
in that auto yard.

16:01.380 --> 16:04.970
You ran out of food
and couldn't feed your baby.

16:05.170 --> 16:06.450
And your son couldn't
shake a cough.

16:06.650 --> 16:08.230
You thought
he had pneumonia.

16:08.430 --> 16:10.090
You're all parents,
aren't you?

16:13.880 --> 16:14.970
What are you
looking at?

16:16.140 --> 16:18.630
Where are our kids?

16:18.830 --> 16:19.810
Where's Adrian?

16:20.010 --> 16:22.550
I don't know any Adrian.I do.

16:22.750 --> 16:24.290
He was here.

16:24.490 --> 16:25.760
Where is he now?

16:27.630 --> 16:29.950
He's dead.

16:30.150 --> 16:31.430
He just wanted to find
his daughter.

16:31.630 --> 16:33.260
He did find her.

16:33.460 --> 16:35.650
She died too.
A long time ago.

16:35.850 --> 16:38.700
Because of you.

16:38.900 --> 16:40.090
Because of what
you made me do.

16:40.290 --> 16:42.570
Turn around.
Now.

16:42.770 --> 16:45.100
[Men speaking indistinctly]

16:45.290 --> 16:48.970
♪

16:49.170 --> 16:52.150
Wait.
You want to find your kids?

16:52.350 --> 16:53.890
She can help.She's with PADRE.

16:54.090 --> 16:57.150
Not anymore.
She's changed.

16:57.350 --> 16:59.980
You expect us
to believe that?

17:00.180 --> 17:03.070
Look,
PADRE's lied to all of us.

17:03.270 --> 17:05.860
I mean,
this is his daughter.

17:06.050 --> 17:08.470
Maybe we can find out
what else he's lied about.

17:08.670 --> 17:11.510
Together.

17:11.710 --> 17:13.780
We'll let the Commander
decide.

17:13.980 --> 17:14.860
Who's the Commander?

17:15.060 --> 17:18.780
♪

17:18.980 --> 17:20.170
Man: Turn around.

17:20.370 --> 17:25.960
♪

17:26.160 --> 17:27.490
Daniel.

17:27.680 --> 17:30.490
♪

17:30.690 --> 17:32.930
Madison?

17:33.120 --> 17:33.970
June?

17:34.170 --> 17:37.100
You're alive.

17:37.300 --> 17:39.320
You know these people?

17:39.520 --> 17:42.110
Give them back
their weapons.

17:42.310 --> 17:44.420
It looks like
we all have nine lives.

17:44.610 --> 17:47.290
♪

17:47.490 --> 17:48.710
We're gonna need them.

17:54.460 --> 17:56.780
[Inhales deeply]
I often considered
the possibility

17:56.970 --> 17:58.950
of you being alive,
Madison,

17:59.150 --> 18:01.560
but not like this.

18:01.760 --> 18:04.300
[Slurps]

18:05.780 --> 18:08.270
[Sighs] Yerba mate.

18:08.460 --> 18:09.960
It's good for
the mental focus.

18:10.160 --> 18:11.440
You want some?

18:11.640 --> 18:12.440
I'm good.

18:12.640 --> 18:14.010
[Slurps] Mm.

18:14.210 --> 18:16.190
I'm not proud
of what I did.

18:16.390 --> 18:17.540
You know,
who I became.

18:17.730 --> 18:19.970
I just want a chance
to make it right.

18:20.170 --> 18:22.630
You and me both.

18:22.830 --> 18:25.760
So maybe we can
help each other.

18:25.960 --> 18:28.110
What makes you
so sure?

18:28.310 --> 18:31.380
We've been looking for
that damn island for years.

18:31.570 --> 18:33.900
If what you're saying
is correct,

18:34.100 --> 18:37.120
you're the best and only shot
these folks have

18:37.320 --> 18:39.470
to get their children
back from PADRE.

18:39.670 --> 18:40.560
They're all parents?

18:40.760 --> 18:42.130
Mm-hmm.

18:42.320 --> 18:44.000
How'd you wind up
with them?

18:44.200 --> 18:45.560
Seven years ago,

18:45.760 --> 18:48.000
Morgan told PADRE
we were out there,

18:48.200 --> 18:49.260
and they found us

18:49.460 --> 18:52.310
and brought everyone to a ship
to assess us

18:52.510 --> 18:54.050
before deciding
where we were gonna be sent

18:54.250 --> 18:58.660
according to our skills
and usefulness.

18:58.860 --> 18:59.930
Some people went
to the mainland.

19:00.120 --> 19:01.930
Others went
to the island.

19:02.130 --> 19:05.060
Others, I don't know
where they went.

19:05.260 --> 19:08.590
PADRE thought that
I was too old to be of any use,

19:08.790 --> 19:10.890
so they dumped me
in the swamp.

19:11.090 --> 19:13.240
[Sighs]
Sorry, Daniel.

19:13.440 --> 19:15.510
Eh. He was right
about one thing.

19:15.710 --> 19:16.900
I was old.

19:17.100 --> 19:18.550
But he wrong about
everything else,

19:18.750 --> 19:21.900
because being old
doesn't mean to be useless.

19:22.100 --> 19:23.250
I can take care
of myself.

19:23.450 --> 19:25.260
So could everyone
in the group.

19:25.450 --> 19:28.130
Except for Charlie.

19:28.330 --> 19:29.600
What happened
to Charlie?

19:31.080 --> 19:32.610
Morgan didn't
mention it?

19:32.810 --> 19:34.090
He didn't get a chance
to tell me much

19:34.290 --> 19:36.090
before PADRE figured out
what we were up to

19:36.290 --> 19:37.740
and separated us.

19:39.220 --> 19:41.490
She was very sick.

19:41.690 --> 19:45.010
She had become like a daughter
to me by then.

19:45.210 --> 19:46.620
I said that I would stay
with her

19:46.820 --> 19:49.670
till the end, so she wouldn't
have to die alone,

19:49.870 --> 19:52.400
like Ofelia.

19:53.970 --> 19:57.200
And I broke my promise.

19:57.400 --> 19:58.720
I wasn't there for her.

19:58.920 --> 20:00.980
I wasn't there for Luciana,
either.

20:02.670 --> 20:04.120
I'm sorry
it happened that way.

20:04.320 --> 20:06.200
I know Morgan
would be too.

20:08.460 --> 20:11.210
I had no purpose.

20:11.410 --> 20:13.650
And then
I found these folks,

20:13.850 --> 20:15.780
this angry,
desperate group of people

20:15.980 --> 20:18.390
in search
of their kidnapped children.

20:19.780 --> 20:22.700
It motivated me,

20:22.900 --> 20:25.230
gave me a reason
to stick around.

20:25.430 --> 20:29.450
So I organized and trained them,
turned them into an army.

20:29.650 --> 20:31.100
Strong,
getting stronger,

20:31.300 --> 20:33.180
because there's more
of them out there.

20:36.060 --> 20:39.550
I lost my family,
Madison.

20:39.750 --> 20:41.510
But I'm gonna fight
with everything I got

20:41.700 --> 20:44.380
to help these folks
get back to theirs.

20:44.580 --> 20:45.680
Maybe you haven't lost
everyone.

20:45.880 --> 20:47.160
The files.

20:47.360 --> 20:48.560
It's not just the kids
in there.

20:48.760 --> 20:49.950
Luciana, Charlie --

20:50.150 --> 20:51.590
you can find out
what happened to them.

20:53.380 --> 20:55.040
Dove: We can use
the prefect transport boat

20:55.240 --> 20:56.600
to get back to
the island.

20:58.820 --> 21:02.130
Dove, are you sure you want
to go down this road?

21:02.330 --> 21:05.140
Maybe you should stop
asking questions

21:05.340 --> 21:07.920
and begin
answering some.

21:08.120 --> 21:09.620
Like what?

21:09.820 --> 21:12.140
Like who else knows
you're PADRE's daughter?

21:12.340 --> 21:13.620
Not many.

21:13.820 --> 21:18.930
How come your father separates
children from their parents,

21:19.130 --> 21:21.010
but he doesn't do
the same to himself?

21:23.490 --> 21:24.590
You don't get it.

21:24.790 --> 21:26.460
Yeah, sure we do.

21:26.660 --> 21:27.990
He's a hypocrite,
like every other asshole

21:28.190 --> 21:28.900
that runs
places like this.

21:29.100 --> 21:30.640
No, he's not.

21:30.840 --> 21:34.300
The way this place is run,
the way we do things,

21:34.500 --> 21:35.950
PADRE believes in it.

21:36.150 --> 21:37.950
Has for a very long time.

21:38.150 --> 21:39.480
What you're saying
doesn't make sense.

21:39.680 --> 21:40.960
She's right.
Why is he sacrificing people

21:41.160 --> 21:42.960
for an experiment
that will never pay off?

21:43.160 --> 21:45.180
It <i>will</i>pay off.

21:45.380 --> 21:47.310
It already is.

21:47.510 --> 21:49.270
Look at Finch.

21:49.470 --> 21:51.360
Madison: What happened
to your father?

21:51.560 --> 21:53.010
Why'd he build a place
like this?

21:53.210 --> 21:55.750
Hey. Come on.
We gotta go.

21:55.950 --> 21:58.880
Where did you come from?
Before you were at PADRE.

22:00.580 --> 22:01.630
I don't know.

22:01.830 --> 22:04.410
Why do you care?

22:04.610 --> 22:06.460
Do you know me?

22:06.660 --> 22:08.540
I've never seen you before
in my life.

22:10.800 --> 22:12.770
Hawk:
Move away from the boat. Now.

22:12.970 --> 22:14.030
♪

22:14.230 --> 22:15.030
Let her go.

22:15.230 --> 22:16.950
You don't understand.

22:17.150 --> 22:18.910
She's PADRE's daughter.

22:19.110 --> 22:20.820
You've been lied to.

22:21.020 --> 22:24.040
PADRE has been ripping
families apart,

22:24.240 --> 22:26.310
and yet, he has kept
his daughter

22:26.510 --> 22:28.660
by his side
all this time.

22:28.860 --> 22:30.480
It's true, Hawk.

22:30.680 --> 22:32.140
She told us herself.

22:32.340 --> 22:35.530
Maybe you should focus more
on getting me out of here.

22:35.730 --> 22:38.490
Dove, you and Wren don't have
to go along with this anymore.

22:38.690 --> 22:40.450
We're going
to the island.Why?

22:40.650 --> 22:42.190
So PADRE can give us
some answers.

22:42.390 --> 22:44.060
Who are you
to question PADRE?

22:44.260 --> 22:45.150
It's not just her, Hawk.

22:45.350 --> 22:47.020
I've seen some shit
today.

22:47.220 --> 22:49.150
At the train.

22:49.350 --> 22:51.370
PADRE has a lot
to explain.

22:51.570 --> 22:53.680
You're not
thinking straight.

22:53.880 --> 22:56.470
I can say the same
for you.

22:56.670 --> 23:00.120
All these people
lost their children to PADRE.

23:00.320 --> 23:01.470
And there are more of them.

23:01.670 --> 23:02.690
Maybe your own parents.

23:02.890 --> 23:04.470
Our parents abandoned us.

23:04.670 --> 23:06.260
Diane: We didn't.

23:06.460 --> 23:07.830
We've been fighting
this whole time.

23:08.020 --> 23:11.050
♪

23:11.250 --> 23:13.050
Daniel:
Why don't you join us?

23:13.250 --> 23:15.400
Fight alongside us.

23:15.600 --> 23:18.790
Dove, just --
just hand her over.

23:18.990 --> 23:22.190
♪

23:22.390 --> 23:24.280
No.

23:24.480 --> 23:25.840
You won't listen to me?

23:26.040 --> 23:29.190
♪

23:29.390 --> 23:32.200
Maybe you'll listen
to PADRE.

23:32.400 --> 23:33.420
We can't let you do that.

23:33.620 --> 23:35.160
Whoa, hey,
what are you doing?

23:35.360 --> 23:36.770
Madison --This can't wait
any longer.

23:36.970 --> 23:38.250
They'll destroy the files
if they know we're coming.

23:38.450 --> 23:39.680
What files?

23:39.880 --> 23:42.600
The ones that tell us
where she came from.

23:42.800 --> 23:45.380
Who her parents are.
Who all of your parents are.

23:45.580 --> 23:47.170
We'll make sure
you never get it.

23:47.370 --> 23:48.300
You're not getting
on that boat.

23:48.500 --> 23:50.520
You'll have to go
through us.

23:50.720 --> 23:53.780
What? You don't think
I'd shoot an old man?

23:53.980 --> 23:55.700
You might.

23:55.900 --> 23:58.920
But would you shoot me?

23:59.120 --> 24:01.400
Madison...

24:01.600 --> 24:02.580
we'll hold them off.
Go.

24:02.780 --> 24:04.490
No,
I'm not leaving Mo.

24:04.690 --> 24:05.540
Get that file.

24:05.730 --> 24:06.710
♪

24:06.910 --> 24:07.970
If you can show her
the truth,

24:08.170 --> 24:10.450
the rest of the kids
will follow.

24:10.650 --> 24:11.890
Go.

24:12.090 --> 24:21.680
♪

24:21.880 --> 24:31.780
♪

24:31.980 --> 24:41.610
♪

24:54.660 --> 24:55.930
♪Dad?

24:56.130 --> 24:57.370
♪

24:57.570 --> 25:00.500
[Grunts]

25:00.700 --> 25:02.680
♪

25:02.880 --> 25:04.380
Dad?

25:04.580 --> 25:06.070
Dad?!

25:06.270 --> 25:08.600
♪

25:08.800 --> 25:10.430
Ben?
Ben, where are you?

25:10.630 --> 25:11.950
Ben: Dad?

25:12.150 --> 25:12.990
Ben,
I can hear you!

25:13.190 --> 25:14.080
Dad?

25:14.280 --> 25:15.130
Ben?!

25:15.330 --> 25:16.690
Dad?!

25:16.890 --> 25:18.960
♪

25:19.160 --> 25:21.000
Follow my voice!

25:21.200 --> 25:22.790
Ben!

25:22.990 --> 25:23.960
Dad!

25:24.160 --> 25:29.580
♪

25:29.780 --> 25:34.710
♪

25:34.910 --> 25:36.580
Sam!

25:36.780 --> 25:38.150
Aah! Help![Walkers growling]

25:38.350 --> 25:39.320
Ben?

25:39.520 --> 25:41.460
Help!

25:41.660 --> 25:43.110
Ben!

25:43.310 --> 25:46.720
[Growling continues]Aah! Aah! Aah!

25:46.920 --> 25:48.550
Aah!

25:48.750 --> 25:51.990
[Gasping]

25:52.190 --> 25:55.210
[Screaming]

25:55.410 --> 25:56.820
Ben!

25:57.020 --> 25:58.650
PADRE: <i>I think it's time</i>
<i>you told the others</i>

25:58.850 --> 26:00.770
<i>where you've been, Finch.</i>

26:03.080 --> 26:04.390
What do you mean?

26:04.590 --> 26:05.830
<i>You were bit.</i>

26:06.030 --> 26:07.240
<i>And you're still here.</i>

26:07.440 --> 26:11.140
<i>Healthy. Thriving.</i>

26:11.340 --> 26:12.970
Where's Red Kite?

26:13.170 --> 26:14.490
And Starling?

26:14.690 --> 26:17.450
<i>They have been reassigned.</i>

26:17.650 --> 26:19.020
Where?

26:19.220 --> 26:22.850
<i>Somewhere they can't</i>
<i>cause you any more harm.</i>

26:23.050 --> 26:24.200
They saved me.

26:24.390 --> 26:26.130
<i>No.</i>

26:26.330 --> 26:28.440
<i>We did.</i>

26:28.640 --> 26:31.380
[Walkie-talkie beeps]
Man: <i>PADRE 1,</i>
<i>we have a situation.</i>

26:31.580 --> 26:33.860
♪

26:34.060 --> 26:37.620
What kind of situation?

26:37.820 --> 26:39.910
Madison:
<i>We have questions.</i>

26:40.110 --> 26:41.910
<i>And we have your daughter.</i>

26:42.110 --> 26:43.740
How about telling your guards
to stand aside

26:43.940 --> 26:46.960
so we can come and have
a little chat with you?

26:47.160 --> 26:49.090
Don't do this, Lark.

26:49.290 --> 26:51.220
No more hiding
behind the mirror.

26:51.420 --> 26:53.050
Time to tell the truth.

26:53.250 --> 26:54.920
He doesn't have to answer
for anything.

26:55.120 --> 26:57.360
Oh, yes, he does.

26:57.560 --> 26:58.930
Every kid deserves to know

26:59.130 --> 27:00.490
why you had them ripped away
from their parents,

27:00.690 --> 27:03.390
and you wouldn't do the same
for your own daughter.

27:03.590 --> 27:06.080
Daniel: <i>Madison,</i>
<i>we got away from them.</i>

27:06.280 --> 27:07.720
<i>Is Dove still with you?</i>

27:07.920 --> 27:09.940
♪

27:10.140 --> 27:11.530
Yes, Daniel.
Why?

27:11.720 --> 27:13.850
<i>One of our people thinks</i>
<i>she might be her mother.</i>

27:14.050 --> 27:22.560
♪

27:22.760 --> 27:23.560
I didn't think
it was possible,

27:23.760 --> 27:24.730
<i>but a mother knows.</i>

27:24.930 --> 27:27.190
Don't fall
for this crap.

27:27.390 --> 27:28.740
<i>Your name is Alex.</i>

27:28.940 --> 27:30.520
A collector took you from me
at a campground

27:30.720 --> 27:32.920
outside Baton Rouge
years ago.

27:33.120 --> 27:34.810
<i>I think</i>
<i>it was that woman, Lark.</i>

27:35.010 --> 27:38.530
<i>I'm not sure,</i>
<i>but I'm sure about you, Alex.</i>

27:38.730 --> 27:39.920
♪

27:40.120 --> 27:41.880
I have searched so long.

27:42.080 --> 27:43.580
♪

27:43.780 --> 27:47.320
I sang "You Are My Sunshine"
to you as they took you away.

27:47.520 --> 27:50.930
♪

27:51.130 --> 27:53.200
<i>I never stopped looking.</i>

27:53.400 --> 27:55.900
This woman
is not your mother.

27:56.100 --> 27:57.550
She's just trying to
get in your head.

27:57.750 --> 27:59.200
Stop lying to her.

27:59.400 --> 28:02.160
I'm not lying.

28:02.360 --> 28:03.990
There's only one way
to find out.

28:04.190 --> 28:06.210
♪

28:06.410 --> 28:07.690
Dove's file.

28:07.890 --> 28:09.520
We want it.

28:09.720 --> 28:11.130
You're making
a mistake.

28:11.330 --> 28:12.870
Do it,

28:13.070 --> 28:14.830
<i>or I tell everyone here </i>
<i>who Shrike really is.</i>

28:15.030 --> 28:21.310
♪

28:21.510 --> 28:22.490
PADRE: <i>Bring her inside.</i>

28:22.690 --> 28:23.920
<i>Give her what she wants.</i>

28:24.120 --> 28:25.320
Copy that.

28:25.520 --> 28:28.890
♪

28:29.080 --> 28:30.840
You're about to get all
the answers you came here for.

28:31.040 --> 28:32.370
Let's go.

28:32.570 --> 28:37.370
♪

28:37.570 --> 28:39.150
Go ahead, Dove.

28:43.630 --> 28:45.470
Shrike: Wait.No more stalling.

28:45.670 --> 28:47.690
There's something you
need to understand before
you read that file.

28:47.890 --> 28:50.730
What's that? We already know
this place is built on a lie.

28:50.930 --> 28:52.210
It's not what you think.

28:52.410 --> 28:53.610
Them what is it?

28:53.800 --> 28:54.870
It's the only way
to protect them.

28:55.070 --> 28:56.430
From what?

28:56.630 --> 28:58.180
From what happened here
before.

28:58.370 --> 29:00.480
♪

29:00.680 --> 29:02.400
And what's that,
PADRE?

29:02.600 --> 29:03.790
What happened here?

29:03.990 --> 29:06.180
<i>I don't answer to you,</i>
<i>Lark.</i>

29:06.380 --> 29:07.530
You always say
you never lost a kid.

29:07.730 --> 29:10.840
I don't know
if that's true.

29:11.040 --> 29:12.710
Who'd you lose?

29:12.910 --> 29:15.320
[Walkers growling][Whimpering]

29:15.520 --> 29:16.370
♪

29:16.570 --> 29:18.460
Ben!No, no, no, no!

29:18.660 --> 29:20.630
[Gunshot]

29:20.830 --> 29:23.110
[Walkers growling]

29:23.310 --> 29:25.030
♪

29:25.230 --> 29:26.860
Krennick:
What are you doing here?

29:27.060 --> 29:28.640
♪

29:28.840 --> 29:30.640
You forgot these.
W-We were worried.

29:30.840 --> 29:32.640
Sam.
We gotta get you out of here.

29:32.840 --> 29:33.860
The shipyard's
full of the dead.

29:34.060 --> 29:35.650
Where's Goddard
and the others?

29:35.850 --> 29:37.260
♪

29:37.460 --> 29:40.570
[Whimpering]

29:40.760 --> 29:43.000
Let's go.

29:43.200 --> 29:44.530
Answer me.

29:44.730 --> 29:46.000
What happened here?

29:47.610 --> 29:49.140
We got to get back
to the boat.

29:49.340 --> 29:50.710
[Walkers growling]

29:50.910 --> 29:52.490
Alright, alright, look...

29:52.690 --> 29:54.970
[Growling continues]

29:55.170 --> 30:00.540
♪

30:00.740 --> 30:03.200
You're never gonna get my father
to admit to anything.

30:03.400 --> 30:06.460
♪

30:06.660 --> 30:08.110
Why is that?

30:08.310 --> 30:09.120
♪

30:09.320 --> 30:11.250
[Growling continues]Sam.

30:11.450 --> 30:13.640
♪

30:13.840 --> 30:15.640
Sam, climb up.
Come on.

30:15.840 --> 30:18.340
[Grunts]

30:18.540 --> 30:19.690
Let's hear it.

30:19.890 --> 30:21.650
♪

30:21.850 --> 30:25.310
[Growling continues][Grunts]

30:25.510 --> 30:27.480
Ben, climb, climb.

30:27.680 --> 30:29.350
[Growling continues]

30:29.550 --> 30:31.220
Why won't he answer us?

30:31.420 --> 30:33.140
♪

30:33.340 --> 30:34.620
Dad!
Give me your hand.

30:34.820 --> 30:36.230
[Growling continues]

30:36.430 --> 30:37.880
Ben.

30:38.080 --> 30:38.930
♪

30:39.130 --> 30:41.280
[Yelling]

30:41.480 --> 30:46.200
♪

30:46.400 --> 30:47.980
Don't let this die.

30:48.180 --> 30:50.070
It's too important.

30:50.270 --> 30:55.290
♪

30:55.490 --> 31:00.470
♪

31:00.670 --> 31:01.990
I love you both.

31:02.190 --> 31:10.310
♪

31:10.510 --> 31:18.660
♪

31:18.860 --> 31:26.980
♪

31:27.180 --> 31:35.110
♪

31:35.310 --> 31:37.200
Shrike:
My father can't answer you.

31:37.400 --> 31:39.950
'Cause my father is dead.

31:40.150 --> 31:46.470
♪

31:46.670 --> 31:49.560
My brother and I lost him
a long time ago.

31:49.760 --> 31:56.180
♪

31:56.380 --> 32:02.580
♪

32:02.780 --> 32:04.800
You wanted to ask
PADRE for the truth.

32:05.000 --> 32:06.840
♪

32:07.040 --> 32:09.280
Go ahead.

32:09.480 --> 32:11.410
Ask us.

32:11.610 --> 32:12.980
We are PADRE.

32:13.180 --> 32:17.580
♪

32:29.420 --> 32:31.210
[Walkers growling]
Madison:
How did it go from what your dad
was doing at that shipyard

32:31.410 --> 32:34.520
to what you're doing here?

32:34.720 --> 32:37.050
We didn't know
how to go on.

32:37.250 --> 32:39.740
[Growling continues]

32:43.740 --> 32:46.660
Sam.

32:46.860 --> 32:48.190
I found it
in the container.

32:48.390 --> 32:50.920
[Growling continues]

33:10.810 --> 33:12.860
What did we even have
to go on for?

33:15.250 --> 33:17.780
Man: <i>PADRE 1, do you copy?</i>

33:17.980 --> 33:27.440
♪

33:27.640 --> 33:29.740
But then
the universe answered.

33:31.050 --> 33:34.150
It was one of the kids
from the island.

33:34.350 --> 33:35.450
He wanted to know
what happened to his parents.

33:35.650 --> 33:36.670
They all did.

33:36.870 --> 33:38.850
And what did you
tell them?

33:39.050 --> 33:40.240
We knew what it would do
to them

33:40.440 --> 33:42.940
if they knew
their parents had died.

33:43.140 --> 33:44.800
How it would break them.

33:46.850 --> 33:49.160
So you lied?

33:49.360 --> 33:51.600
We told them their parents
abandoned them.

33:51.800 --> 33:53.690
That they knew they couldn't
take care of them, so they fled.

33:53.890 --> 33:55.340
And they believed you?

33:55.540 --> 33:58.170
Well, their parents left
and never came back.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.390
What else were they
supposed to think?

34:00.590 --> 34:03.130
We told them we'll face
this new world together,

34:03.330 --> 34:05.130
without our parents...Yeah.

34:05.330 --> 34:07.140
...that we'll be better
for it.

34:07.340 --> 34:08.700
And the shipyard?

34:08.900 --> 34:10.140
Those containers?

34:10.340 --> 34:12.970
Our father died
protecting what was inside.

34:13.170 --> 34:14.970
We made sure
it stayed that way.

34:15.170 --> 34:18.190
How?That doesn't concern you.

34:18.390 --> 34:20.930
How did you recruit adults?
You were just a bunch of kids.

34:21.130 --> 34:22.460
It was easy.

34:22.660 --> 34:24.940
We made them believe
he was still here.

34:25.140 --> 34:28.590
And they kept on
believing.

34:28.790 --> 34:30.060
Why did you lie?

34:32.540 --> 34:33.550
To protect you.

34:33.750 --> 34:35.070
From what?

34:36.630 --> 34:38.200
Open it.

34:43.160 --> 34:45.080
Go on.
It's what you wanted.

35:05.320 --> 35:06.720
Go on.

35:06.920 --> 35:08.620
Tell Dove who she is.

35:10.490 --> 35:11.980
♪

35:12.180 --> 35:13.510
Her name was Odessa.

35:13.710 --> 35:17.860
♪

35:18.060 --> 35:20.910
She cried when you pulled her
from me on the beach.

35:21.100 --> 35:23.430
No.
What's wrong?

35:23.630 --> 35:24.650
Shrike: Go on, Lark.

35:24.850 --> 35:26.780
She deserves the truth.

35:26.980 --> 35:28.220
♪

35:28.420 --> 35:29.610
Your name is Odessa.

35:29.810 --> 35:31.440
My name?

35:31.640 --> 35:36.270
♪

35:36.470 --> 35:37.360
My parents?

35:37.560 --> 35:39.580
♪

35:39.780 --> 35:41.620
I knew your mother.

35:41.820 --> 35:44.410
Her name was Ava.

35:44.610 --> 35:46.020
What happened to Ava,
Lark?

35:46.220 --> 35:53.890
♪

35:54.090 --> 35:55.420
She died.

35:55.620 --> 35:57.990
♪

35:58.190 --> 35:59.380
How?

35:59.580 --> 36:05.470
♪

36:05.670 --> 36:08.000
She was trying
to take you back from PADRE.

36:08.200 --> 36:09.260
♪

36:09.460 --> 36:12.000
And who made her believe
that was possible?

36:12.200 --> 36:13.700
♪

36:13.900 --> 36:16.350
We can help you
and your baby.

36:16.550 --> 36:17.610
How?

36:17.810 --> 36:19.530
♪

36:19.730 --> 36:23.400
My mother is dead
because of you?

36:23.600 --> 36:24.930
♪

36:25.130 --> 36:27.710
My mother is dead
because of you?!

36:27.910 --> 36:29.060
Dove, no.

36:29.260 --> 36:30.630
You made me believe
in something more.

36:30.830 --> 36:32.850
Let go.Dove.

36:33.050 --> 36:34.630
Let her go, Dove.

36:34.830 --> 36:36.550
She needs to pay
for this.

36:36.750 --> 36:37.720
She will.

36:37.920 --> 36:40.220
But not this way.

36:40.420 --> 36:41.770
<i>Guards.</i>

36:41.970 --> 36:44.550
♪

36:44.750 --> 36:46.900
Crane: Stand down, Dove.

36:47.100 --> 36:48.430
Stand down.

36:48.630 --> 36:54.170
♪

36:54.370 --> 36:55.570
What are you
gonna do now?

36:55.760 --> 36:57.860
We're going to continue
what we started at the train.

36:59.080 --> 37:00.090
Like hell you are.

37:00.290 --> 37:02.310
You don't have a choice,
Blue Jay.

37:02.510 --> 37:03.880
You...

37:04.080 --> 37:05.620
are a monster.

37:05.820 --> 37:08.190
No.

37:08.390 --> 37:10.360
My brother and I
are protecting these kids

37:10.560 --> 37:13.240
from the worst pain
of all.

37:13.430 --> 37:15.110
The pain of losing
a parent.

37:15.310 --> 37:17.070
What does that have to do
with the train?

37:17.260 --> 37:18.890
The experiments?

37:19.090 --> 37:21.550
As long as the world
is the way it is,

37:21.750 --> 37:26.200
children will continue
to experience unimaginable loss.

37:26.400 --> 37:31.210
But if there's a cure,
that would change everything.

37:31.410 --> 37:32.560
We could go back to family.

37:32.760 --> 37:33.690
Right.

37:33.890 --> 37:35.560
To connection.

37:35.760 --> 37:37.960
But in the meantime, we're going
to protect these kids

37:38.150 --> 37:39.520
the way we always have.

37:39.720 --> 37:49.050
♪

37:49.250 --> 37:52.970
You want to tell the kids
you rescued the truth?

37:53.170 --> 37:55.150
Go ahead.

37:55.350 --> 37:56.840
Let the whole island hear.

37:57.040 --> 38:01.850
♪

38:02.050 --> 38:03.500
That's what I thought.

38:03.700 --> 38:10.730
♪

38:10.930 --> 38:18.390
♪

38:18.590 --> 38:25.950
♪

38:43.140 --> 38:45.240
What were they like?Nick,
Alicia.

38:45.440 --> 38:48.060
After the stadium,
when they thought I was dead.

38:52.240 --> 38:54.460
I don't think
you would've recognized them.

39:00.810 --> 39:02.040
Alright.

39:02.240 --> 39:03.860
Let's go.

39:11.780 --> 39:14.000
We got to stop meeting
like this.

39:15.870 --> 39:19.270
♪

39:19.470 --> 39:22.450
Let our people go,
and we will walk away.

39:22.650 --> 39:25.320
No one has to get hurt.

39:25.520 --> 39:28.850
I got another 12 soldiers
deep in the woods.

39:29.050 --> 39:30.720
And we got your prefects.

39:30.920 --> 39:32.370
You wouldn't.

39:32.570 --> 39:33.980
You want to take
that chance?

39:34.180 --> 39:40.990
♪

39:41.190 --> 39:47.950
♪

39:48.150 --> 39:54.960
♪

39:55.160 --> 40:01.970
♪

40:02.170 --> 40:03.710
Alex.

40:03.910 --> 40:06.060
♪

40:06.260 --> 40:08.630
That isn't my name.

40:08.830 --> 40:10.980
And you are not
my mother.

40:11.180 --> 40:12.240
My mother's dead.

40:12.440 --> 40:14.240
♪

40:14.440 --> 40:15.630
Because of her.

40:15.830 --> 40:17.850
♪

40:18.050 --> 40:20.770
June: You can still have
a family, Dove.

40:20.970 --> 40:23.560
Even if it's not
the one you thought.

40:23.760 --> 40:25.560
You said Madison made you
believe in something more.

40:25.760 --> 40:28.650
That's still there.

40:28.850 --> 40:30.210
Come with us.

40:30.410 --> 40:35.700
♪

40:35.900 --> 40:38.180
Looks like
she made her choice.

40:38.380 --> 40:39.220
And every other kid
on that island

40:39.420 --> 40:42.050
is gonna make
that same one.

40:42.250 --> 40:44.320
Remember that.

40:44.510 --> 40:47.060
No, they won't.

40:47.260 --> 40:48.320
You'll see.

40:48.520 --> 40:53.540
♪

40:53.740 --> 40:56.460
I'm sorry, Daniel.

40:56.660 --> 40:58.160
♪

40:58.350 --> 41:00.550
This was a mistake.
She can't help us.

41:00.750 --> 41:02.460
Yes, she can.She's right.

41:02.660 --> 41:04.030
Those kids are never gonna
follow me,

41:04.230 --> 41:06.770
not after everything
I've done.

41:06.970 --> 41:08.080
Not just them.

41:08.280 --> 41:10.430
♪

41:10.630 --> 41:13.560
Yeah, I'm not
the leader you need.

41:13.760 --> 41:16.830
But I think I know
who might be.

41:17.030 --> 41:18.830
Who's that?

41:19.030 --> 41:20.700
Your father.

41:20.900 --> 41:29.140
♪

41:29.340 --> 41:37.800
♪

41:38.000 --> 41:40.490
[Walkers growling]

41:55.460 --> 41:56.940
Crane, do you copy?

41:58.340 --> 42:00.780
Crane, do you copy?

42:00.980 --> 42:02.180
Crane: <i>Yeah, I copy.</i>

42:02.380 --> 42:04.000
Where are you?
I told you to meet me.

42:04.200 --> 42:06.270
Being out in the open
didn't seem like a good idea

42:06.470 --> 42:08.050
after what happened today.

42:08.250 --> 42:09.310
<i>We've got a bigger problem.</i>

42:09.510 --> 42:11.100
The parents know
where the island is,

42:11.300 --> 42:13.970
<i>which means it's only a matter</i>
<i>of time until they get there.</i>

42:14.170 --> 42:16.210
They'll destroy everything
we've built.

42:16.410 --> 42:18.630
<i>Not if we're not here.</i>

42:18.830 --> 42:20.540
What are you
talking about?

42:20.740 --> 42:22.980
It doesn't matter
if they know who we are.

42:23.180 --> 42:26.680
What matters is that
what we've built survives.

42:26.880 --> 42:28.200
How are we
gonna do that?

42:28.400 --> 42:31.120
By expanding.

42:31.320 --> 42:33.420
We're gonna do what Dad said.

42:33.620 --> 42:35.970
There are thousands of Carrion
in that shipyard,

42:36.170 --> 42:38.340
<i>Carrion we put there</i>
<i>to protect what's inside.</i>

42:38.540 --> 42:40.780
[Growling continues]

42:40.980 --> 42:42.850
♪

42:43.050 --> 42:45.570
<i>We taught the kids</i>
<i>how to fight for a reason.</i>

42:45.770 --> 42:48.220
It's time they showed us
what they've learned.

42:48.420 --> 42:50.700
[Growling continues]

42:50.900 --> 42:56.220
♪

42:59.750 --> 43:03.720
♪

43:03.920 --> 43:06.070
PADRE thinks you came out here
for a reason.

43:06.270 --> 43:07.850
Nowhere to go, Morgan.

43:08.050 --> 43:09.770
[Walkers growling]What is it?

43:09.960 --> 43:12.290
They're trying to burn us out.
Ready?

43:12.490 --> 43:13.380
PADRE's got your son.

43:13.580 --> 43:14.680
You know what
we have to do.

43:14.880 --> 43:16.120
Mo: Dad! Help me!

43:16.320 --> 43:17.430
I waited too long.

43:17.620 --> 43:18.860
♪

43:19.060 --> 43:20.170
Listen, baby,
I'm coming for you.

43:20.370 --> 43:21.470
They will kill you

43:21.670 --> 43:23.000
if you don't tell them
what happened.

43:23.200 --> 43:28.690
♪

43:40.000 --> 43:41.270
♪We shouldn't be in here.

43:41.470 --> 43:43.970
[Tapping]

43:44.170 --> 43:46.720
PADRE:
<i>What are you doing in here?</i>
[Both gasp]

43:46.910 --> 43:49.720
[Laughs] "What are you
doing in here?"

43:49.920 --> 43:52.020
Dad. Not funny.

43:52.220 --> 43:55.810
The third episode really
kind of lifts the veil on PADRE.

43:56.010 --> 43:58.200
They were kind of trying
to rewrite the way we live.

43:58.400 --> 43:59.950
Come with me.

44:00.150 --> 44:02.300
I want to show you guys
something.

44:02.500 --> 44:04.520
A woodpecker?

44:04.710 --> 44:06.560
So?
What's the big deal?

44:06.760 --> 44:08.870
These birds,
they live in families.

44:09.070 --> 44:11.090
They cooperate
to raise their young.

44:11.290 --> 44:12.740
If they can do it,
so can we.

44:12.940 --> 44:15.400
Chambliss: It was all rooted
in connection,

44:15.600 --> 44:18.440
the very thing that PADRE now
is trying to eradicate.

44:18.640 --> 44:20.310
I want you to use
those code names I gave you.

44:20.510 --> 44:22.230
Why do I
have to be Shrike?

44:22.430 --> 44:23.970
'Cause a shrike may be small,

44:24.170 --> 44:26.230
but it is brutal
when it needs to be.

44:26.430 --> 44:28.580
It doesn't hesitate
to look after its family.

44:28.780 --> 44:32.200
And what this episode does
is kind of unpack

44:32.390 --> 44:36.550
how something with such
kind of benevolent beginnings

44:36.750 --> 44:38.980
could be perverted
in such a way

44:39.180 --> 44:42.210
that it could be kind of
this unrecognizable force

44:42.400 --> 44:44.900
that we know
in the present day.

44:45.100 --> 44:46.850
[Growling]

44:48.380 --> 44:50.430
After everything
PADRE gave you,

44:50.630 --> 44:51.910
you betrayed him.

44:52.110 --> 44:54.130
This is how you're gonna
make it up to him.

44:54.330 --> 44:55.960
[Growling]

44:56.160 --> 44:58.480
Goldberg:
Mo is on this path of --

44:58.680 --> 45:00.350
of trying
to bring PADRE down.

45:00.550 --> 45:02.230
And more specifically,

45:02.420 --> 45:05.270
she believes that she's gonna
do it with Madison.

45:05.470 --> 45:07.970
I need to do this.

45:08.170 --> 45:09.450
Dove: Do what?

45:09.650 --> 45:11.280
We need to see
what's in there.

45:11.480 --> 45:14.410
Maybe PADRE isn't
telling us the truth.

45:14.610 --> 45:17.850
Goldberg: And then Shrike,
one of PADRE's emissaries,

45:18.050 --> 45:19.940
is here doing
these weird experiments.

45:20.140 --> 45:22.380
Shrike, what the hell
is going on here?

45:22.580 --> 45:24.730
I am protecting
what PADRE's built.

45:24.930 --> 45:26.600
I'm ensuring you kids
have a future,

45:26.800 --> 45:28.690
a future --Is that what this
looks like to you?

45:28.890 --> 45:32.210
Suddenly, that -- that doesn't
ring very good for Dove,

45:32.410 --> 45:34.870
because that's not
keeping people safe.

45:35.070 --> 45:36.480
Tell them
to get over here.

45:36.680 --> 45:37.610
Madison:
Don't do it, Dove.

45:37.810 --> 45:39.000
Why not?

45:39.200 --> 45:40.610
PADRE lied about this.

45:40.810 --> 45:42.270
Think about what else
he's lied to you about.

45:42.460 --> 45:43.960
Your parents, they could
still be out there,

45:44.160 --> 45:45.490
and I can help you
find them.

45:45.690 --> 45:48.450
It really sets Dove
on this trajectory of,

45:48.640 --> 45:50.190
"Have I been lied to?"

45:50.390 --> 45:52.840
What's PADRE actually doing
behind the scenes?

45:53.040 --> 45:54.710
Woman: Hands up!

45:54.910 --> 45:57.630
Tell us what we want to know.
Nobody has to get hurt.

45:57.830 --> 45:59.670
♪

45:59.870 --> 46:01.460
Daniel.

46:01.660 --> 46:03.720
Goldberg: Daniel's fate
has been unknown.

46:03.920 --> 46:06.990
We haven't seen where he's been
the past seven years.

46:07.190 --> 46:10.860
PADRE thought that I was
too old to be of any use,

46:11.060 --> 46:13.170
so they dumped me
in the swamp.

46:13.370 --> 46:17.080
We see that Daniel is --
is using sort of all of these

46:17.280 --> 46:21.520
different aspects of his past,
his skills, for good.

46:21.720 --> 46:23.310
I lost my family,
Madison.

46:23.510 --> 46:25.660
But I'm gonna fight
with everything I got

46:25.860 --> 46:27.920
to help these folks
get back to theirs.

46:28.120 --> 46:29.660
Dove: We can use
the prefect transport boat

46:29.860 --> 46:31.140
to get back
to the island.

46:31.340 --> 46:35.360
♪

46:35.560 --> 46:38.890
[Box thuds]Madison: Go ahead, Dove.

46:39.090 --> 46:40.890
Shrike: Wait.No more stalling.

46:41.090 --> 46:42.370
There's something
you need to understand

46:42.570 --> 46:43.460
before you read
that file.

46:43.660 --> 46:45.590
And what's that, PADRE?

46:45.790 --> 46:47.070
What happened here?

46:47.270 --> 46:49.070
PADRE: <i>I don't answer</i>
<i>to you, Lark.</i>

46:49.270 --> 46:54.990
♪

46:55.190 --> 46:57.600
Madison's actions
of smashing that mirror

46:57.800 --> 47:01.690
are all about kind of unmasking
the truth behind PADRE.

47:01.890 --> 47:04.350
Why did you lie?

47:04.550 --> 47:06.570
To protect you.
From what?

47:06.770 --> 47:11.270
The expectation is that it
will kind of deflate the message

47:11.470 --> 47:13.050
that PADRE's tried to create.

47:13.250 --> 47:15.140
But what we actually learn,
you know,

47:15.340 --> 47:16.930
by the end of this episode

47:17.120 --> 47:22.150
is that it doesn't actually
kind of destroy PADRE's message.

47:22.350 --> 47:26.850
In fact, it --
it reinforces it.

47:27.050 --> 47:30.070
Go on.
Tell Dove who she is.

47:30.270 --> 47:32.460
She deserves the truth.

47:32.660 --> 47:34.930
My parents?

47:36.020 --> 47:38.210
I knew your mother.

47:38.410 --> 47:39.900
Her name was Ava.

47:40.100 --> 47:42.430
♪

47:42.630 --> 47:44.300
She died.

47:44.500 --> 47:45.910
Shrike: How?

47:46.110 --> 47:49.170
♪

47:49.370 --> 47:52.740
She was trying
to take you back from PADRE.

47:52.940 --> 47:55.750
And who made her believe
that was possible?

47:55.950 --> 47:58.880
We can help you
and your baby.

47:59.080 --> 48:03.090
My mother is dead...
because of you?

48:04.350 --> 48:06.540
My mother is dead?!
[Shouting]

48:06.740 --> 48:08.240
Let her go, Dove.

48:08.440 --> 48:09.800
She needs to pay
for this.

48:10.000 --> 48:12.590
She will.
But not this way.

48:12.790 --> 48:14.240
PADRE is an idea,

48:14.440 --> 48:16.940
and, you know, an idea
can oftentimes be

48:17.140 --> 48:19.120
more powerful
than one person.

48:19.320 --> 48:22.990
♪

48:23.190 --> 48:27.130
You want to tell
the kids you rescued the truth?

48:27.330 --> 48:28.560
You...

48:28.760 --> 48:30.520
are a monster.

48:30.720 --> 48:32.650
No.

48:32.850 --> 48:35.220
My brother and I
are protecting these kids

48:35.420 --> 48:37.830
from the worst pain of all --

48:38.030 --> 48:39.790
the pain of losing
a parent.

48:39.990 --> 48:47.350
♪

49:03.330 --> 49:12.740
♪

49:12.940 --> 49:22.170
♪
